&lt;li&gt;Polymorphism&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Abstraction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Encapsulation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is a class?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
A class is a collection of methods and variables. It defines the data and the behaviour of a type. It is like a blueprint or template from which objects are created. A class is declared once. A class doesn&amp;rsquo;t allocated memory when it is created.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is an object?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
An object is an instance of a class. An object is created many times per requirement. Object allocates memory when it is created. An object consists of :&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>